# qlmanage
# 
#   QuickLook server tool.
#   More information: https://keith.github.io/xcode-man-pages/qlmanage.1.html.
# 
#   Display QuickLook for one or multiple files:
$ qlmanage -p path/to/file1 path/to/file2 ...
#   Compute 300px wide PNG thumbnails of all JPEGs in the current directory and put them in a directory:
$ qlmanage *.jpg -t -s 300 path/to/directory
#   Reset QuickLook:
$ qlmanage -r

# show the full list of filetype -> qlgenerator assignments/registrations
$  qlmanage -m


# The qlmanage -g command is used to specify a particular generator for
# Quick Look to use when generating previews or thumbnails for a file.
# This can be useful when you have multiple generators that claim to
# handle the same file type and you want to force the use of a specific
# one.
# 
# For example, if you want to force the use of a generator located at
# /System/Library/QuickLook/Office.qlgenerator for a file named myDoc, you
would use the following command:
$ qlmanage -p -g /System/Library/QuickLook/Office.qlgenerator myDoc
# x
# This command tells qlmanage to use the specified generator for
# generating a preview of myDoc.

